Indonesia Stocks: Harum Energy, International Nickel, Garuda

-- B y   F e m i   A d i
-- 
2011-04-13T09:47:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/indonesia-stocks-adaro-energy-aneka-tambang-medco-energi.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 15.18 points, or 0.4
percent, to 3,734.41.  PT Harum Energy (HRUM IJ), an Indonesian coal producer,
rose 0.6 percent to 9,150 rupiah. Harum was rated “neutral” in
new coverage at Credit Suisse Group AG. The brokerage has a
share-price forecast of 9,600 rupiah, according to a report by
Fonny Surya.  PT International Nickel  Indonesia  (INCO IJ), the nation’s
biggest producer of the metal, gained 0.5 percent to 4,900
rupiah. The company’s shareholders approved a dividend of $148
million to be paid in May, said Fabio Bechara, a company
director.  PT Garuda Indonesia (GIAA IJ), the nation’s biggest carrier,
rose 1.9 percent to 550 rupiah. Oil traded near its lowest in
two weeks on signs prices are damaging fuel demand and that
political tension in Middle East may abate. A lower oil price
may help reduce the airline’s fuel costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
